TypeSignature.Value: .class public interface auto ansi abstract ThreeDFormat implements class Microsoft.Office.Core._IMsoDispObj

Docs.summary: Represents a shape's three-dimensional formatting.

remarks.para: Use the property to return a ThreeDFormat object.

You cannot apply three-dimensional formatting to some kinds of shapes, such as beveled shapes or multiple-disjoint paths. Most of the properties and methods of the ThreeDFormat object for such a shape will fail.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Creator As Integer
public: property int Creator { int get(); };

Docs.summary: Returns a 32-bit integer that indicates the application in which this object was created.

remarks.para: If the object was created in Microsoft Excel, this property returns the string XCEL, which is equivalent to the hexadecimal number 5843454C.
The Creator property is designed to be used in Microsoft Excel for the Macintosh, where each application has a four-character creator code. For example, Microsoft Excel has the creator code XCEL.

MemberSignature.Value: .method public hidebysig newslot virtual instance void IncrementRotationX([in]float32 Increment) runtime managed

Docs.param: Required Single. Specifies how much (in degrees) the rotation of the shape around the x-axis is to be changed. Can be a value from –90 through 90. A positive value tilts the shape up; a negative value tilts it down.
Docs.summary: Changes the rotation of the specified shape around the x-axis by the specified number of degrees.

remarks.para: Use the property to set the absolute rotation of the shape around the x-axis.

You cannot adjust the specified shape's rotation around the x-axis past the upper or lower limit for the RotationX property (90 degrees to –90 degrees). For example, if the RotationX property is initially set to 80 and you specify 40 for the argument, the resulting rotation will be 90 (the upper limit for the RotationX property) instead of 120.
To change the rotation of a shape around the y-axis, use the method. To change the rotation around the z-axis, use the method.

MemberSignature.Value: .method public hidebysig newslot virtual instance void ResetRotation() runtime managed

Docs.summary: Resets the extrusion rotation around the x-axis and the y-axis to 0 (zero) so that the front of the extrusion faces forward.

remarks.para: This method doesn’t reset the rotation around the z-axis.

To set the extrusion rotation around the x-axis and the y-axis to anything other than 0 (zero), use the and properties of the object. To set the extrusion rotation around the z-axis, use the property of the object that represents the extruded shape.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property float RotationX { float get(); void set(float value); };

Docs.summary: Returns or sets the rotation of the extruded shape around the x-axis in degrees.

remarks.para: The RotationX property can be a value from –90 through 90. A positive value indicates upward rotation; a negative value indicates downward rotation.

To set the rotation of the extruded shape around the y-axis, use the property of the object. To set the rotation of the extruded shape around the z-axis, use the Rotation property of the object. To change the direction of the extrusion’s sweep path without rotating the front face of the extrusion, use the method.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property float RotationY { float get(); void set(float value); };

Docs.summary: Returns or sets the rotation of the extruded shape around the y-axis in degrees.

remarks.para: The RotationY property can be a value from –90 through 90. A positive value indicates rotation to the left; a negative value indicates rotation to the right.

To set the rotation of the extruded shape around the x-axis, use the property of the object. To set the rotation of the extruded shape around the z-axis, use the Rotation property of the object. To change the direction of the extrusion’s sweep path without rotating the front face of the extrusion, use the method.

To set the rotation of the extruded shape around the y-axis, use the property of the object. To set the rotation of the extruded shape around the x-axis, use the property of the ThreeDFormat object. To change the direction of the extrusion's sweep’s path without rotating the front face of the extrusion, use the method.
